05044nam a22008655i 9789048550678DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20202020ne     fo  d z      eng d  a97890485506787 a10.1515/97890485506782doi  a(DE-B1597)548861  a(OCoLC)1146545532  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anecNL 4aDG540.8.C43bV47 2020 7aBIO0140002bisacsh04a940.21 aVester, Matthew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aTransregional Lordship and the Italian Renaissance :bRené de Challant, 1504-1565 /cMatthew Vester. 1aAmsterdam : bAmsterdam University Press, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (330 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aRenaissance History, Art and Culture ;v500tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tMaps and Tables -- tAbbreviations -- tAcknowledgments -- t1. On the edge of the Italian Renaissance -- t2. René's early career to 1536 -- t3. René's growing influence during the war years, 1536-1553 -- t4. René and Duke Emanuel Filibert -- t5. Kinship and noble life -- t6. The Challant political networks -- t7. Finance and brokerage -- t8. Lordship -- t9. The embodiment of spatial politics -- tAbout the author -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aRené de Challant, whose holdings ranged from northwestern Italy to the Alps and over the mountains into what is today western Switzerland and eastern France, was an Italian and transregional dynast. The spatially-dispersed kind of lordship that he practiced and his lifetime of service to the house of Savoy, especially in the context of the Italian Wars, show how the Sabaudian lands, neighboring Alpine states, and even regions further afield were tied to the history of the Italian Renaissance. Situating René de Challant on the edge of the Italian Renaissance helps us to understand noble kin relations, political networks, finances, and lordship with more precision. A spatially inflected analysis of René's life brings to light several themes related to transregional lordship that have been obscured due to the traditional tendencies of Renaissance studies. It uncovers an 'Italy' whose boundaries extend not just into the Mediterranean, but into regions beyond the Alps.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aNobilityzItalyvBiography. 0aRenaissancezItaly. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aInternational Relations. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Royalty.2bisacsh  aItaly, Renaissance, Challant, Savoy, lordship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048550678zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048550678423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048550678.jpg  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  